    <briefdescription>
<para>Armijo line search. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Let <formula id="156">$ \alpha $</formula> and <formula id="303">$ \beta $</formula> be 2 scalars in  <formula id="304">$ [0,1]
$</formula>. Let <formula id="28">$ x $</formula> be the current value of the unknown,  <formula id="305">$ d
$</formula> the search direction and <formula id="183">$ t $</formula> the step. Let <formula id="82">$ f $</formula> be the function to minimize. The line search stops when  <formula id="306">$ t
$</formula> verifies <formula id="307">\[ f(x + t \cdot d) - f(x) \leq -\alpha t f&apos;(x+t \cdot d) \]</formula> and  <formula id="308">\[ f(x+\frac{t}{\beta} \cdot d) - f(x) &gt; -\frac{\alpha}{\beta}
    t f&apos;(x+t \cdot d) \]</formula></para>
<para>(see Polak, Algorithms and consistent approximations, Optimization, volume 124 of Applied Mathematical Sciences, Springer-Verlag, NY, 1997) </para>
    </detaileddescription>
